<br>
I am currently working on obtaining my second set of AA abilities and am wondering if there is any (good) reason why you wouldn't max Combat Stability? (My current thought is to max Combat Stability and then work on Durability).<br>
<br>
I have spoken to two warriors about their AA, and both have 2 points into Combat Stability and a smattering of others in other abilities.  Since the boost for the third rank of Combat Stability is an extra 5% (you get 5% for two ranks of Combat Stability (2% for first and 3% for the second)), it would seem that the third rank is important because it would take you from 5% extra damage mitigation to 10% of extra damage mitigation.  Given these numbers, it would appear that you get more out of a third point in Combat Stability than you would with other abilities.<br>
<br>
Any thoughts?<br>
<br>
